The Minister of Mines and Steel Development Mr Olamilekan Adegbite and the Minister of state Mr Uchechukwu Ogah have assumed duty with the promise to increase the revenue base of the country with solid minerals. In his opening remarks, Mr Adegbite said one of their major tasks is to increase the revenue base of the country to help lift 100million Nigerians from poverty as proposed by the President. “I intend along with my brother (Minister of State) to learn the ropes quickly so that we can contribute our quota to the success of this administration especially by increasing the revenue base of the country and lifting people out of poverty,”Adegbite said. In his remarks, the Minister of State, Mr Uchechukwu Ogah said with the support of everyone, they will take the ministry to an enviable height. In his handing over speech, the Permanent Secretary Dr Abdulkadir Mu’azu said the Ministry of Mines and Steel Development (MMSD) is strategic in the economic diversification drive of the country. Science & tech key to diversifying economy – Minister Ministers tasked on revival of manufacturing sector Mining sector still at ‘potential stage’ Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin